WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.520 --> 00:00:07.410
A speaker like Dr. Zakir Naik can only seem
persuasive in an atmosphere of ignorance.

00:00:07.410 --> 00:00:12.199
Put him in a room full of people who’ve
carefully studied the Bible and the Qur’an,

00:00:12.199 --> 00:00:15.910
and they will laugh him off the stage.

00:00:15.910 --> 00:00:22.180
Watch what happens when we take a closer look
at one of Naik’s claims.

00:00:22.180 --> 00:00:27.580
According to Naik, Jesus prophesied the coming
of Muhammad in the Book of John, Chapter 14,

00:00:27.580 --> 00:00:28.580
Verse 16:

00:00:28.580 --> 00:00:33.120
It’s further mentioned in the Gospel of
John, Chapter Number 14, verse number 16,

00:00:33.120 --> 00:00:39.470
Jesus Christ (Peace Be Upon Him) says: “I
will pray to my Father, to send you another

00:00:39.470 --> 00:00:42.079
Comforter, who will abide with you forever.”

00:00:42.079 --> 00:00:46.829
Let’s go ahead and read the verse—John
14:16.

00:00:46.829 --> 00:00:47.899
Jesus says:

00:00:47.899 --> 00:00:53.700
“I will ask the Father, and He will give
you another Helper, that He may be with you

00:00:53.700 --> 00:00:55.030
forever.”

00:00:55.030 --> 00:00:58.610
Notice that Jesus refers to the Father here.

00:00:58.610 --> 00:01:01.460
Do Muslims refer to Allah as “Father”?

00:01:01.460 --> 00:01:05.829
No they don’t, because according to the
Qur’an, Allah is a Father to no one.

00:01:05.829 --> 00:01:11.399
So even before we consider the meaning of
the verse, we see that it already contradicts

00:01:11.399 --> 00:01:13.319
Islam.

00:01:13.319 --> 00:01:18.310
But we’ll let Naik slide on that one, because
he’s about to thoroughly expose Muhammad

00:01:18.310 --> 00:01:20.250
as a false prophet.

00:01:20.250 --> 00:01:22.579
Explain the verse for us, Dr. Naik.

00:01:22.579 --> 00:01:27.299
Jesus Christ (Peace Be Upon Him) says in the
Gospel of John, Chapter Number 14, verse Number

00:01:27.299 --> 00:01:32.709
16, that I will pray to My Father to send
you another Comforter, who will abide with

00:01:32.709 --> 00:01:33.709
you forever.

00:01:33.709 --> 00:01:37.670
That means Jesus Christ (Peace Be Upon Him)
will not abide with the Christians forever.

00:01:37.670 --> 00:01:43.359
This new Comforter, this new prophet who will
come, will abide with you forever.

00:01:43.359 --> 00:01:45.959
So the verse is talking about a prophet.

00:01:45.959 --> 00:01:47.219
That’s interesting.

00:01:47.219 --> 00:01:50.630
The verse doesn’t say anything about a prophet.

00:01:50.630 --> 00:01:56.530
But that’s what Dr. Naik is for—to tell
us what Jesus really means.

00:01:56.530 --> 00:02:01.630
Now, there are all kinds of things we could
say in response to Naik’s interpretation

00:02:01.630 --> 00:02:02.630
here.

00:02:02.630 --> 00:02:08.020
We could point out that he’s defending Muhammad
by quoting a book that opens with a clear

00:02:08.020 --> 00:02:10.470
declaration of the deity of Christ.

00:02:10.470 --> 00:02:16.970
“In the beginning was the Word, and the
Word was with God, and the Word was God.

00:02:16.970 --> 00:02:19.220
He was in the beginning with God.

00:02:19.220 --> 00:02:24.670
All things came into being through Him, and
apart from Him nothing came into being that

00:02:24.670 --> 00:02:27.040
has come into being.”

00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:32.500
So all created things came into being through
the Word.

00:02:32.500 --> 00:02:35.070
What else did the Word do?

00:02:35.070 --> 00:02:36.070
Verse 14:

00:02:36.070 --> 00:02:42.410
“And the Word became flesh, and dwelt among
us, and we saw His glory, glory as of the

00:02:42.410 --> 00:02:46.950
only begotten from the Father, full of grace
and truth.”

00:02:46.950 --> 00:02:49.460
This is referring, of course, to Jesus.

00:02:49.460 --> 00:02:52.630
That’s how the Gospel of John begins.

00:02:52.630 --> 00:02:58.460
Towards the end of the Gospel of John, Jesus’
Apostle Thomas calls him “My Lord and my

00:02:58.460 --> 00:02:59.710
God!”

00:02:59.710 --> 00:03:04.570
The Book of John also proclaims Jesus’ death
and resurrection.

00:03:04.570 --> 00:03:10.110
Strange book for Muslims to go to when they
try to convince people that Islam is true.

00:03:10.110 --> 00:03:14.750
That’s where the atmosphere of ignorance
comes in handy.

00:03:14.750 --> 00:03:17.970
But we’ll ignore all of that.

00:03:17.970 --> 00:03:22.570
We could also point out that in the very chapter
Naik is quoting, Jesus says:

00:03:22.570 --> 00:03:29.370
“I am the way, and the truth, and the life;
no one comes to the Father but through Me.”

00:03:29.370 --> 00:03:30.460
Odd.

00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:35.980
Three of Allah’s ninety-nine names are “the
Way,” “the Truth,” and “the Living.”

00:03:35.980 --> 00:03:41.819
But let’s pretend that Jesus doesn’t apply
the names of Allah to himself in the chapter

00:03:41.819 --> 00:03:43.760
Naik quotes.

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:48.820
We could note that right there in the chapter
Naik quotes, Jesus claims that he can answer

00:03:48.820 --> 00:03:49.820
prayers.

00:03:49.820 --> 00:03:54.050
He tells his followers that he’s returning
to the Father, and He says:

00:03:54.050 --> 00:03:59.790
“Whatever you ask in My name, that will
I do, so that the Father may be glorified

00:03:59.790 --> 00:04:01.200
in the Son.”

00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:02.769
What’s that?

00:04:02.769 --> 00:04:07.740
Father and Son, and the Son is going to answer
the prayers of the apostles?

00:04:07.740 --> 00:04:09.890
Is this sounding like Islam yet?

00:04:09.890 --> 00:04:13.610
Certainly not, but we can ignore all of this.

00:04:13.610 --> 00:04:18.239
Naik tells us that the Helper—the Comforter—is
Muhammad.

00:04:18.239 --> 00:04:20.840
What else does Jesus say about the Comforter?

00:04:20.840 --> 00:04:26.699
Well, Jesus immediately identifies the Helper
as “the Spirit of truth.”

00:04:26.699 --> 00:04:29.509
Was Muhammad a spirit, according to Islam?

00:04:29.509 --> 00:04:34.999
Jesus says that the world cannot receive the
Spirit “because it does not see Him.”

00:04:34.999 --> 00:04:38.900
Was Muhammad invisible, according to Islam?

00:04:38.900 --> 00:04:43.949
Jesus says to his first-century followers:
“But you know Him . . .” Did they know

00:04:43.949 --> 00:04:49.719
Muhammad? “. . . because He abides with
you . . .” Muhammad abided with Jesus’

00:04:49.719 --> 00:04:53.740
first-century followers? “. . . and will
be in you.”

00:04:53.740 --> 00:04:57.060
Was Muhammad in Jesus’ first-century followers?

00:04:57.060 --> 00:05:01.919
Doesn’t sound anything like Muhammad.

00:05:01.919 --> 00:05:03.050
But guess what.

00:05:03.050 --> 00:05:07.960
You can show all of this to one of Zakir Naik’s
fans and ask, “Is there any way this can

00:05:07.960 --> 00:05:10.159
be referring to Muhammad?”

00:05:10.159 --> 00:05:15.520
And he’ll respond, with a straight face,
“Yes, it’s obviously talking about Muhammad.

00:05:15.520 --> 00:05:20.840
Muhammad is the only person Jesus could possibly
be talking about here.”

00:05:20.840 --> 00:05:26.120
So instead of banging our heads against the
impenetrable wall of ignorance and stupidity

00:05:26.120 --> 00:05:32.129
that Naik has built around the minds of his
followers, let’s just agree with him . . . for

00:05:32.129 --> 00:05:34.110
the sake of argument.

00:05:34.110 --> 00:05:39.990
Let’s pretend that Jesus was actually talking
about Muhammad in John 14:16.

00:05:39.990 --> 00:05:44.410
We can’t get any more generous than that,
can we?

00:05:44.410 --> 00:05:50.259
Amazingly, even when we’re as generous as
we can possibly be, Naik still ends up refuting

00:05:50.259 --> 00:05:52.979
Islam and supporting Christianity.

00:05:52.979 --> 00:05:53.979
How so?

00:05:53.979 --> 00:05:59.879
Well, Naik doesn’t just quote what Jesus
says about the Comforter in John 14:16.

00:05:59.879 --> 00:06:03.689
He also quotes what Jesus says in John 16:7.

00:06:03.689 --> 00:06:06.319
What does Jesus say there, Dr. Naik?

00:06:06.319 --> 00:06:10.529
It’s further mentioned in the Gospel of
John, Chapter Number 16, Verse Number 7, Jesus

00:06:10.529 --> 00:06:15.710
Christ (Peace Be Upon Him) says: “Nevertheless,
I tell you the truth, it is expedient for

00:06:15.710 --> 00:06:16.990
you that I go away.

00:06:16.990 --> 00:06:19.150
For if I go not away the Comforter shall not
come.

00:06:19.150 --> 00:06:21.500
For if I depart, shall I send Him.”

00:06:21.500 --> 00:06:22.529
What did Jesus say?

00:06:22.529 --> 00:06:25.069
“For if I depart, shall I send Him.”

00:06:25.069 --> 00:06:27.729
Who sends the Comforter, according to Jesus?

00:06:27.729 --> 00:06:29.879
“For if I depart, shall I send Him.

00:06:29.879 --> 00:06:31.879
Shall I send Him.

00:06:31.879 --> 00:06:32.940
Shall I send Him.”

00:06:32.940 --> 00:06:39.089
Quick question for Muslims: Who sent Muhammad
as a prophet?

00:06:39.089 --> 00:06:44.629
Any Muslim will be happy to say that Allah
sent Muhammad as a prophet.

00:06:44.629 --> 00:06:48.189
So, according to Islam, Allah sent Muhammad.

00:06:48.189 --> 00:06:51.189
Muhammad was sent by Allah.

00:06:51.189 --> 00:06:57.669
Now, according to Jesus, and according to
Zakir Naik, because he quoted the verse as

00:06:57.669 --> 00:07:02.050
an authoritative prophecy, who sends the Comforter?

00:07:02.050 --> 00:07:04.860
I’ll remind you that Jesus says:

00:07:04.860 --> 00:07:10.319
“But I tell you the truth, it is to your
advantage that I go away; for if I do not

00:07:10.319 --> 00:07:17.639
go away, the Helper will not come to you;
but if I go, I will send Him to you.”

00:07:17.639 --> 00:07:20.860
Who sends the Comforter?

00:07:20.860 --> 00:07:22.919
Jesus does.

00:07:22.919 --> 00:07:26.050
So Jesus sends the Comforter.

00:07:26.050 --> 00:07:29.369
The Comforter is sent by Jesus.

00:07:29.369 --> 00:07:31.009
Allah sends Muhammad.

00:07:31.009 --> 00:07:34.310
Muhammad is sent by Allah.

00:07:34.310 --> 00:07:41.449
If the Comforter is Muhammad, as Zakir Naik
claims, who does that make Jesus?

00:07:41.449 --> 00:07:50.649
Hallelujah!

00:07:50.649 --> 00:07:56.639
Thank you, Dr. Naik, for admitting that Jesus
is your God, and the God of Muhammad, and

00:07:56.639 --> 00:07:59.110
the God of all Muslims.

00:07:59.110 --> 00:08:04.830
Now, since Zakir Naik has proven, conclusively,
that Jesus is God, our Muslim friends are

00:08:04.830 --> 00:08:06.889
faced with quite a dilemma.

00:08:06.889 --> 00:08:11.219
Jesus is God, but the Qur’an says that Jesus
is not God.

00:08:11.219 --> 00:08:13.550
This means one of two things.

00:08:13.550 --> 00:08:18.499
Either Muhammad was not a true prophet, because
Muhammad delivered the Qur’an, which falsely

00:08:18.499 --> 00:08:24.490
asserts that Jesus is not God; or Muhammad
was a true prophet, in which case he must

00:08:24.490 --> 00:08:30.630
have originally proclaimed that Jesus is God,
only to have his revelations corrupted by

00:08:30.630 --> 00:08:32.169
later Muslims.

00:08:32.169 --> 00:08:37.710
So, according to Zakir Naik, either Muhammad
was a false prophet, or he was a true prophet,

00:08:37.710 --> 00:08:42.300
but Muslims corrupted the book that he delivered.

00:08:42.300 --> 00:08:47.390
Muslims don’t want to say that the Qur’an
has been corrupted, so we can only conclude

00:08:47.390 --> 00:08:50.890
that Muhammad was a false prophet.

00:08:50.890 --> 00:08:56.130
Since Muhammad was a false prophet, we can
ignore all of Zakir Naik’s nonsense about

00:08:56.130 --> 00:09:03.680
the Comforter being Muhammad, and we can acknowledge
that the Comforter is the Holy Spirit.

00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:05.180
But it gets better.

00:09:05.180 --> 00:09:08.400
Because Jesus tells us more about the Holy
Spirit.

00:09:08.400 --> 00:09:11.060
Jesus says, in John 15:26:

00:09:11.060 --> 00:09:17.710
“When the Helper comes, whom I will send
to you from the Father, that is the Spirit

00:09:17.710 --> 00:09:22.660
of truth who proceeds from the Father, He
will testify about Me.”

00:09:22.660 --> 00:09:26.550
Here again, the Spirit is sent by Jesus.

00:09:26.550 --> 00:09:28.580
But this is no ordinary Spirit.

00:09:28.580 --> 00:09:30.770
This isn’t a created spirit.

00:09:30.770 --> 00:09:34.060
This is the Spirit who proceeds from the Father.

00:09:34.060 --> 00:09:39.650
And if the Spirit is in Jesus’ followers,
wherever they are, anywhere they go, even

00:09:39.650 --> 00:09:46.960
if they travel across the universe, then the
Spirit has a divine attribute: omnipresence.

00:09:46.960 --> 00:09:51.690
This reminds me of what King David said in
Psalm 139, verses 7 to 8:

00:09:51.690 --> 00:09:53.990
“Where can I go from Your Spirit?

00:09:53.990 --> 00:09:56.430
Or where can I flee from Your presence?

00:09:56.430 --> 00:10:02.830
If I ascend to heaven, You are there;
If I make my bed in Sheol, behold, You are

00:10:02.830 --> 00:10:03.830
there.”

00:10:03.830 --> 00:10:09.380
If the Spirit has a divine attribute, then
the Spirit is divine.

00:10:09.380 --> 00:10:12.150
And yet Jesus sends the Spirit.

00:10:12.150 --> 00:10:16.970
Zakir Naik has already admitted that Jesus
is God, but now we have further proof.

00:10:16.970 --> 00:10:20.830
Jesus sends the Spirit of God.

00:10:20.830 --> 00:10:25.120
But how can God send the Spirit of God, which
proceeds from the Father?

00:10:25.120 --> 00:10:29.770
It’s as if the Islamic view of God is too
simplistic to account for this.

00:10:29.770 --> 00:10:33.340
And we find the same thing in the Old Testament.

00:10:33.340 --> 00:10:38.740
In Isaiah 48:16, Yahweh (the God of Israel)
is speaking, and he says:

00:10:38.740 --> 00:10:44.910
“Come near to Me, listen to this:
From the first I have not spoken in secret,

00:10:44.910 --> 00:10:48.180
From the time it took place, I was there.

00:10:48.180 --> 00:10:54.510
And now the Lord God has sent Me, and His
Spirit.”

00:10:54.510 --> 00:10:59.830
So God says that he’s been sent by God,
along with the Spirit of God.

00:10:59.830 --> 00:11:04.420
And yet the Bible consistently affirms that
there’s only one God.

00:11:04.420 --> 00:11:09.860
And this goes all the way back to the very
first chapter of the Bible, where God says

00:11:09.860 --> 00:11:11.620
in Genesis 1:26:

00:11:11.620 --> 00:11:16.870
“Let Us make man in Our image, according
to Our likeness.”

00:11:16.870 --> 00:11:19.830
Who’s God talking to?

00:11:19.830 --> 00:11:22.780
He’s not talking to the angels.

00:11:22.780 --> 00:11:25.390
The angels didn’t create man.

00:11:25.390 --> 00:11:27.430
God created man.

00:11:27.430 --> 00:11:31.910
And yet the one God who created man is somehow
plural.

00:11:31.910 --> 00:11:36.590
God declared in the very first chapter of
the Bible that he is one in one sense, but

00:11:36.590 --> 00:11:39.430
more than one in another sense.

00:11:39.430 --> 00:11:45.780
And he gave us more and more insight into
his nature in the rest of the Bible.

00:11:45.780 --> 00:11:50.250
By the time we get to the Book of John, we
can’t even understand what’s going on

00:11:50.250 --> 00:11:52.790
without the doctrine of the Trinity.

00:11:52.790 --> 00:11:58.600
And this is where Zakir Naik goes when he
wants to convince his listeners that Islam

00:11:58.600 --> 00:12:01.390
is the true religion.

00:12:01.390 --> 00:12:05.920
Now think about the utter incompetence of
Muslim apologists like Zakir Naik.

00:12:05.920 --> 00:12:09.110
He tries to prove that Muhammad was a prophet
of God.

00:12:09.110 --> 00:12:14.420
But as he tries to prove that Muhammad was
a prophet of God, he accidently proves that

00:12:14.420 --> 00:12:19.780
Jesus is God, that God is a Trinity—Father,
Son, and Holy Spirit—and that Muhammad was

00:12:19.780 --> 00:12:21.600
a false prophet.

00:12:21.600 --> 00:12:28.790
Zakir Naik and Ahmed Deedat before him, spent
their lives deceiving their gullible and ignorant

00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:29.790
listeners.

00:12:29.790 --> 00:12:35.820
But as they spoke, they did get some important
Bible verses into the minds of their followers.

00:12:35.820 --> 00:12:41.640
These verses are the seeds that we get to
water until Muslims recognize the truth about

00:12:41.640 --> 00:12:43.230
Jesus.

00:12:43.230 --> 00:12:48.170
One of the most important things we can do
is to draw out the logical implications of

00:12:48.170 --> 00:12:54.110
